    <text>
        <body>
            <div frus:doc-dateTime-max="1935-09-02T05:25:00-05:00"
                frus:doc-dateTime-min="1935-09-02T05:25:00-05:00" n="648"
                subtype="historical-document" type="document" xml:id="d648">
                <note rend="inline" type="source">884.6363 African Exploration and Development
                    Corp./3: Telegram</note>
                <head>
                    <hi rend="italic">The Chargé in Ethiopia</hi> (<persName type="from">
                        <hi rend="italic">Engert</hi>
                    </persName>) <hi rend="italic">to the <gloss type="to">Secretary of
                            State</gloss>
                    </hi>
                </head>
                <opener>
                    <dateline rendition="#right">
                        <placeName>
                            <hi rend="smallcaps">Addis Ababa</hi>
                        </placeName>, <date calendar="gregorian" when="1935-09-02T13:00:00+02:35"
                            >September 2, 1935—1 p.m.</date>
                        <lb/> [Received September 2—12:20 p.m.]</dateline>
                </opener>
                <p>86. My 84, August 30, noon. In reply to questions from my colleagues and the
                    press I have consistently maintained the concession was a purely commercial
                    matter without any political significance whatever and that neither the American
                    Government nor this Legation had taken part in the negotiations. I should be
                    glad to have the Department’s approval and guidance.</p>
                <p>I understand Rickett, who signed on behalf of the company, tried also to obtain
                    contract for Lake Tsana project but was referred to the White Corporation.<note
                        n="95" xml:id="d648fn95">The J. G. White Engineering Corporation, of New
                        York.</note>
                </p>
                <closer>
                    <signed>
                        <hi rend="smallcaps">Engert</hi>
                    </signed>
                </closer>
            </div>
        </body>
